post_text:
Changes to Harambee’s Public Board meetings due to COVID-19 Coronavirus Pandemic

Due to Pennsylvania governmental guidelines surrounding the COVID-19 CORONA VIRUS outbreak, Harambee Institute of Science and Technology Charter School’s in person public Board meetings were cancelled for the months of March and April.

Harambee Institute of Science and Technology Charter School will hold a public Board meeting on May 27, 2020 from 5:00 - 6:00 PM. The public is invited to attend via Zoom video. Anyone wishing to attend the Board meeting should send an email request to board@histcs.org no later than 5:00 PM on Tuesday May 26, 2020 to join the meeting.

As we enter summer break, we’d like to share the mission and vision that was developed and adopted by the Board of Directors for our watoto and our work: African centered education is concerned with the origins, current status, and future of the African world. Our daily interactions prepare students to participate as global citizens, helping them develop the skills to deal with all types of people with a clear awareness of “who I am and where I am from.” Harambee envisions a collective and informed African American community utilizing science and technology as a means of promoting self-reliance both locally and in the wider world. [ 426 more words ]

Congratulations to Mama Robin L H James, the Art Walimu here at Harambee!

Through her hard work and dedication, Mama Robin was able submit a proposal to our community partner, Philadelphia Museum of Art, which allowed Harambee to be involved in the 2018 Art Partners Program and the 2018 Delphi Art Program.

Harambee was one of five schools to be selected!

ASANTE SANA MAMA ROBIN for your HARD WORK and DEDICATION in ensuring all of our watoto here at Harambee have the best experiences in the world of ART!

ASE'! ASE'! ASE'!

"The pouring of libation in African rituals must be performed for such entrance in the tsiefe-ancestral land. The transcendent kinship beyond death is very important in the overall purposes of the ritual of libation."

On this day, we can't forget those who have become our ancestors. Those that have paved the pathway of TRUTH, LIGHT, and LOVE. We can not forget that time where the FOUNDERS of our LEGACY passed on into ETERNITY. Today, WE WILL BE THANKFUL! BE BLESSED! BE HUMBLED! BE TRUE!

HARAMBEE! HARAMBEE! HARAMBEE!

Our goal is to raise $35K in the next five weeks to provide the following projects for Fall 2017:
Reading Intervention Programming: Read 180
New Classroom Furniture
Additional Partnerships and After-School Clubs including Chess, Debate, and Journalism.
Can we count on you? Contributions are tax-deductible and can be made to:
Harambee Charter School (640 North 66th Street, Philadelphia, PA 19151)
OR
https://paypal.me/friendsofharambee

General Ticket Admission: $20 in advance. $25 at the door.

This scene of Pursuit of Happiness is where Chris (Will Smith)takes his son, to play basketball and tells him to never give up on his dreams.

We as a people can NEVER GIVE UP! We have the blood of our ancestors running through our veins. We have VICTORY running through our veins. We have SELF-RELIANCE running through of veins.

WE ARE KINGS! WE ARE QUEENS!

Why should we ever want to give up?

IT'S NOT IN OUR DNA!
